LAGOS – Lagos State chapter of the New Nigerian Peoples Party (NNPP) has held their senatorial primary election in all the three senatorial districts of the State. The primary elections, monitored by Daily Independent took place in Ikorodu for Lagos East; 28 Bishop Crowther Street in Surulere host the Lagos Central while the party’s local govt secretariat, Alimosho, 91, Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway, Pako Bus-Stop, off Iyana Ipaja, was the venue for Lagos West Senatorial zone. The candidates who emerged by consensus are Mr Ralph Iloke for the Lagos Central; Mr Lawal Nurudeen for Lagos East, and Hon Mustapha Oladapo Dabiri for Lagos West. -Advertisement- The State Chairman, Chief Adisa Falade congratulated all the candidates and promised them maximum support before, during and after the 2023 general elections. The election was observed by officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), security agents and several journalists. The party’s presidential candidate, Engr Dr. Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, was ably represented by Dr. Abubakre who delivered his good will message, while the former State Chairman, Mallam Shakirudeen Olamilekan Olofin, urged the party supporters to utilise the window opened by the INEC to get their Permanent Voter Cards (PVCs) before the closure of the exercise on June 30, 2022. The party’s State Secretary, Mr Sheriff Oladejo, promised to ensure that campaigns of the candidates would be widely publisised in traditional and social media. The Returning Officer for Lagos Central was Mr Richard Benson, while Favour Bernard acted as the Secretary, Lagos East had Mr Abudulhakeem Onimago as the Returning Officer and Mr Rasheed Dada, as the Secretary. POLL While, the Returning Officer for Lagos West was Barrister Ruth Arukwe, and Mr Ajiboye, the secretary of NNPP Alimosho local government chapter was the Secretary, Electoral Committee.